  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "1. Related Diversification: Building on Existing Strengths",
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "1. Related Diversification: Building on Existing Strengths",
        "formatting": {
          "bold": true
        },
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      }
    ],
    "metadata": {}
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "The evaluation of future growth strategies include both related diversification and unrelated diversification. Related diversification involves the company diversifying into an additional industry that has a common bond with its current business. This common bond could be either the technology or production processes used by the company; or it could be the customers served by the company.",
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The evaluation of future growth strategies ",
        "formatting": {},
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "include",
        "formatting": {},
