        }
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": " both related diversification and unrelated diversification. Related diversification involves the company diversifying into an additional industry that has a common bond with its current business. This common bond could be either the technology or production processes used by the company; or it could be the customers served by the company.",
        "formatting": {},
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      }
    ],
    "metadata": {}
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "The advantage of growing through related diversification is that the company can use its current skills, technology, etc., to grow. It provides the company with the potential for improved efficiencies and cost savings.  The disadvantage of growing through related diversification is that there is likely to be a smaller number of opportunities for growth than if the company pursues unrelated diversification",
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The advantage of growing through related diversification is that the company can use its current skills, technology, etc., to grow. It provides the company with the potential for improved efficiencies and cost savings. ",
