  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "2. Unrelated Diversification: Entering New Growth AreasUnrelated diversification means entering industries that are completely different from the company’s current businesses. Sectors like fintech and digital healthcare fall into this category.",
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "2. Unrelated Diversification: Entering New Growth Areas",
        "formatting": {
          "bold": true
        },
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Unrelated diversification means entering industries that are completely different from the company’s current businesses. Sectors like fintech and digital healthcare fall into this category.",
        "formatting": {},
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      }
    ],
    "metadata": {}
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "One major benefit of this strategy is spreading risk. If one industry performs poorly, the company can rely on other sectors for stability. On the other hand, this approach is more challenging. The company may not have the required knowledge or experience in these new sectors. Managing very different types of businesses can also increase complexity and lead to inefficiencies. Without proper understanding, the chances of failure are higher.",
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "One major benefit of this strategy is spreading risk. If one industry performs poorly, the company can rely on other sectors for stability. On the other hand, this approach is more challenging. The company may not have the required knowledge or experience in these new sectors. Managing very different types of businesses can also increase complexity and lead to inefficiencies. Without proper understanding, the chances of failure are higher.",
